node.text: President Joe Biden announced that he is directing the Secretary of Education to take legal action, when necessary, against governors who try to block mask mandates in schools. Why is the president threatening governors instead of fixing the disaster in Afghanistan? Florida Gov. Ron DeSantis will respond TONIGHT on “Hannity.”

node.text: Secretary of Defense Lloyd Austin told reporters today that the U.S. can’t “collect large numbers of people” fleeing Afghanistan. It’s clear that the Biden team didn’t have a plan for this situation and now they’re in crisis. TONIGHT on "Hannity,” Donald Trump Jr. and Sen. Lindsey Graham will react to the crisis in Afghanistan. Tune in at 9 PM ET or set your DVR to never miss an episode!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Sean Hannity on August 18, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, standing, outdoors and text that says 'AFGHAN INTERPRETER SPEAKS OUT AS TALIBAN TAKES OVER Hannity'.

node.text: HANNITY EXCLUSIVE: An Afghan interpreter living in the U.S. will speak with “Hannity” TONIGHT about the Taliban's takeover of Afghanistan, where his family is trapped. We made a promise to our Afghan allies and interpreters that we would get them and their families out of harm’s way. Tune in at 9 PM ET or set your DVR for this EXCLUSIVE interview!

node.text: HANNITY EXCLUSIVE: What’s happening in Afghanistan is a massive failure and the Biden administration needs to answer several tough questions. Rather than taking responsibility and offering solutions, President Joe Biden blamed former President Donald Trump! node.text: White House Press Secretary Jen Psaki refused to guarantee that the U.S. would evacuate Americans stuck in Afghanistan after August 31. We cannot leave our fellow Americans behind! TONIGHT on “Hannity,” we’ll bring you expert analysis and reactions to the Biden administration’s disastrous withdrawal from Afghanistan.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Sean Hannity on August 17, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text.

node.text: National Security Advisor Jake Sullivan admitted to reporters that the Taliban has a “fair amount” of abandoned U.S. weapons. That’s what happens when you leave a country after 20 years and don’t have an exit strategy! Now the Taliban has control of the country and is already terrorizing the people of Afghanistan. TONIGHT on “Hannity,” we’ll discuss the Biden administration’s failures in Afghanistan.
